SIMPLE: feeler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feeler
<hw>Feel"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, feels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the sense organs or
certain animals (as insects), which are used in testing objects by touch
and in searching for food; an antenna; a palp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Insects . . . perpetually feeling and searching before them with
their <qex>feelers</qex> or antenn⟦ae⟧.</q>
<rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything, as a proposal, observation, etc., put
forth or thrown out in order to ascertain the views of others; something
tentative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feeling</ent>⟦br⟧
